task.summary: - fix text color - add footer - replace dummy text with beautiful lorem ipsium (dummy?) paragraphs.
Add anchors to various points in the page. Handle bootstrap's variable size navbar and anchors via javascript/jquery.
Set project default encodings to UTF-8.
Refactor things in JS. Delete all the libraries. Make the items in navbar stay horizontal instead of stacked for higher zoom levels.

Add a damn progress bar. ALWAYS USE SIZES IN CSS.
A.L.W.A.Y.S.!!!!!!!!!!
Scrolling to an anchor from the navbar is now animated. Deprecate/comment the on-resize/load dynamically sized anchor.

Cancel the scroll animation (to anchor) from jquery when the user scrolls by another means: click, mousewheel scroll, keyboard press, etc. Make the scroll animation shorter: from 1900ms -> to 900ms. Thanks @holographic for the bug report.
